      <section>
        <h2>1. Agreement to Terms</h2>
        <p>These Terms of Service constitute a legally binding agreement made between you, whether personally or on behalf of an entity ("you", "client"), and <strong>Aegis AI</strong> ("we", "us", "our"), concerning your access to and use of our website <strong>https://aegisai.ae</strong> and any custom AI development, training workshops, and strategy services provided by us.</p>
        <p>By accessing the site or engaging our services, you agree that you have read, understood, and agree to be bound by all of these Terms of Service. If you do not agree with all of these terms, you are prohibited from using the site and must discontinue use immediately.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>2. Services Offered</h2>
        <p>We provide technology consultancy services tailored to Small and Medium Enterprises (SMEs) in Dubai and the wider UAE, specializing in:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Custom AI Development:</strong> Designing and deploying bespoke AI agents, WhatsApp chat automation, databases, and operational dashboards integrated with client workflows.</li>
          <li><strong>AI Training &amp; Workshops:</strong> Delivering departmental upskilling workshops in English and Arabic to ensure internal team adoption.</li>
          <li><strong>AI Strategy &amp; Consulting:</strong> Creating 12-month roadmaps, ROI calculations, and vendor-neutral technology audits.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>All specific deliverables, timelines, and payment terms will be defined in a separate signed Statement of Work (SOW) or Service Agreement, which shall take precedence in case of any conflict with these generic terms.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>3. The 100% Refund Guarantee Policy</h2>
        <div class="guarantee-box">
          <p class="title">Zero-Cost Risk-Free Guarantee</p>
          <p>We are proud to offer Dubai's only complete refund policy for custom AI development and workshops. Our guarantee is subject to the following standard parameters to protect both parties:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Defined Success Criteria:</strong> Every project features clear, objectively measurable milestones defined in writing inside the Statement of Work (SOW) before work commences.</li>
            <li><strong>Active Engagement:</strong> The client must provide the necessary credentials, document samples, and attend scheduled alignment sessions required to build the system.</li>
            <li><strong>Guarantee Trigger:</strong> If, at the final delivery stage of the initial defined scope, the custom system or training fails to meet the pre-agreed success criteria despite active collaboration, the client is entitled to request a 100% refund of all development fees paid to date.</li>
            <li><strong>IP Protection:</strong> Upon trigger of a full refund, all licenses, built software code, custom configurations, and intellectual property developed during the project remain the sole property of Aegis AI and cannot be utilized by the client.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>4. Third-Party API Fees &amp; Retainers</h2>
        <p>Unless explicitly written in the SOW, project fees do not include direct third-party usage fees (e.g., API charges from OpenAI, Anthropic, Microsoft Azure, Make.com, or Meta WhatsApp Business API). These are set up directly on the client's billing accounts or billed transparently at cost with zero mark-up.</p>
        <p>Our development projects include <strong>90 days of complimentary post-launch support</strong> (bug fixes, performance monitoring). Ongoing updates, operational retainer packages, and additional training modules are subject to separate monthly agreements — contact us for details.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>5. Intellectual Property Rights</h2>
        <p>Unless otherwise agreed in a signed SOW, upon full and final payment of all invoices, the client is granted a perpetual, worldwide, non-exclusive, non-transferable license to use the custom software, workflows, and configurations developed specifically for their organization.</p>
        <p>Aegis AI retains all rights to our pre-built software modules, underlying frameworks, training methodologies, and proprietary AI agents developed prior to or outside of the specific SOW.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>6. Client Responsibilities</h2>
        <p>To ensure timely project delivery (typically 8–12 weeks), the client agrees to provide:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Accurate data sources, process sheets, and sample documents required for training custom LLMs.</li>
          <li>Timely reviews, feedback, and operational approvals within 3 business days of milestone presentations.</li>
          <li>Departmental access for training workshops to ensure staff participation.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Delays caused by prolonged failure to provide access or responses may result in adjustment of final launch timelines.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>7. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>To the maximum extent permitted by UAE law, Aegis AI shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, or consequential damages, including loss of profits, revenue, data, or business interruption, arising out of the use or inability to use our custom AI systems, even if we have been advised of the possibility of such damages. Our total liability under any SOW shall not exceed the total fees paid by the client under that specific SOW.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>8. Governing Law &amp; Jurisdiction</h2>
        <p>These Terms of Service and your relationship with us shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the Emirate of Dubai and the federal laws of the United Arab Emirates.</p>
        <p>Any dispute arising out of or in connection with these Terms, including any question regarding its existence, validity, or termination, shall be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of the Emirate of Dubai.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>9. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>To resolve a complaint regarding the services or to receive further information regarding the terms of service, please contact us at:</p>
        <div class="contact-box">
          <p><strong style="color:#00253b;">Aegis AI</strong></p>
          <p>Dubai, United Arab Emirates</p>
          <p><strong>Email:</strong> hello@aegisai.ae</p>
          <p><strong>WhatsApp Support:</strong> +971 4 321 8888</p>
        </div>
      </section>

    </div>
  </div>
</main>

